
[1]converging

   CONVERGING, ppr. Tending to one point; approaching each other, as lines
   extended.

   Converging rays, in optics, those rays of light, which proceeding from
   different points of an object, approach, meet and cross, and become
   diverging rays.

   Converging series, in mathematics, is that in which the magnitude of
   the several terms gradually diminishes.
